text:
A general view north from No. 74 Trinity Place, between Rector and Thames Streets, showing the New York Telephone Building, No. 14 West St. between Vesey and Barclay Streets; in the center, the Hudson River and the Sixth Ave. Elevated line running north on Church Street. This set, consisting of three views taken at the same time, are more or less similar. One includes a portion of the 28-story West Street Building on its left.

August 20, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.
title: General view - [Manhattan - Trinity Place - Between Rector and Thames Streets.]
